    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-08-06T15:39:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-08-06T15:39:00-05:00" n="421"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                <head>421. Telegram From the Department of State to the Embassy in the Congo<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d421fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1964–66, DEF 19–8 US–THE
                        CONGO. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SWE_1">Schaufele</persName>;
                        cleared by Colonels <persName corresp="#p_KJF_1">Kennedy</persName> and
                            <persName corresp="#p_LWE_1">Lang</persName> of <gloss target="#t_DOD_1"
                            >DOD</gloss>, Officer in Chargé of Belgian Affairs <persName
                            corresp="#p_MJP_1">Jay P. Moffat</persName>, and McElhiney; and approved
                        by <persName corresp="#p_FJW_1">Fredericks</persName>. Repeated to Brussels,
                            <gloss target="#t_CINCSTRIKE_1">CINCSTRIKE</gloss>, and <gloss
                            target="#t_DOD_1">DOD</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-08-06T16:39:00-04:00">August 6, 1965, 4:39 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>142. Embtels 228<note n="2" xml:id="d421fn2">Telegram 228 from Leopoldville,
                        August 4, transmitted the text of a letter from <persName corresp="#p_TMK_1"
                            >Tshombe</persName> stating that General <persName corresp="#p_MJD_1"
                            >Mobutu</persName> informed him that the United States had decided to
                        withdraw the C–130 aircraft that had been assisting the Congolese forces for
                        many months. <persName corresp="#p_MJD_1">Mobutu</persName> emphasized the
                        grave consequences that would result from their departure, and <persName
                            corresp="#p_TMK_1">Tshombe</persName> asked U.S. authorities to review
                        this decision and agree to prolong their stay until the end of the year.
                        (Ibid.) The remaining two U.S. C–130s left the Congo on August 18.</note>
                    and 232;<note n="3" xml:id="d421fn3">Dated August 4. (Ibid.)</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Deptel_1">Deptel</gloss> 2520;<note n="4" xml:id="d421fn4"
                        >Dated May 12. (Ibid., DEF 19–3 US–THE CONGO)</note> STR J–3 OM 5730 (June
                        9).<note n="5" xml:id="d421fn5">Not found.</note> You requested inform
                        <persName corresp="#p_TMK_1">Tshombe</persName> that due to other
                    commitments and under utilization aircraft US regrets it unable reply favorably
                    to his request retain C–130’s in Congo. You should remind him of arrival C–123
                    which will help fill gap. <gloss target="#t_FYI_1">FYI</gloss> only. US willing
                    if sufficient prior notice given and in your judgment sufficient urgency exists
                    to allow C–130’s which regularly transit <gloss target="#t_Leo_1">Leo</gloss> to
                    stop over briefly to provide internal lift. Obviously if real crisis occurs
                        <gloss target="#t_USG_1">USG</gloss> willing consider request temporary
                    detail one or more C–130’s to Congo. End <gloss target="#t_FYI_1"
                    >FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RDE_1">Rusk</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
